nib.text:
A man was critically injured during a shooting at a gas station in Payne-Phalen early Wednesday morning, officials said.

Shortly before 12:30 a.m., police responded to a report of a shooting in the 300 block of East Wheelock Parkway, at a BP gas station.

Upon arrival, officers found a 19-year-old man with a gunshot wound to the chest.

Medics transported him to a local hospital, where he was listed in critical condition, [WCCO reported](https://minnesota.cbslocal.com/2022/03/30/st-paul-payne-phalen-gas-station-shooting/).

No arrests have been made. This investigation is ongoing.

nib.text:
A Lunds & Byerlys in downtown St. Paul was damaged Tuesday morning after a fire spread to the front of the building and activated the sprinklers inside, officials said. 

At around 1:30 a.m., firefighters responded to a report of a trash fire in the 200 block of E. 10th Street.

Upon arrival, crews discovered the flames had spread to the front of the building and had activated the sprinklers inside.

Crews were eventually able to bring the fire under control without any injuries or damage to the interior of the store or apartments above. 

However, the fire caused significant damage to the exterior of the building and the sprinkler system did damage some of the interior.

The store is to temporarily close pending repairs, according to a statement from the Lunds & Byerlys Downtown management. 

According to a statement from the STFD, investigators suspect the fire was intentionally set.
